      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A rectangular <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">stele</rs>, with a simply moulded panel on the front face, supporting a rougly cut hemisphere—probably cut down to serve as a Moslem tombstone. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.35</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.70</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.325</measure>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> within the panel (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.23</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.35</measure>) which is chipped to the right.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>Rough and irregular, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.02-0.025</measure>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0301" notAfter="0400">Fourth century</date> or later (<rs type="criteria">content</rs>).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
		<ab>
		<lb n="1"/><persName key="zoetus1" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Ζωητός">Ζωητὸς</name></persName><lb n="2"/><persName type="aphrodisian" key="theopemptus1" full="yes"><name reg="Θεόπεμπτος">Θεοπ<unclear reason="damage">εμπ</unclear>
		<lb n="3" type="worddiv"/>του</name></persName> <w lemma="ὄλβιος">ὄλβιον</w>
		<lb n="4"/><w lemma="βίος">βίον</w> <w lemma="ζηλόω">ζηλ<unclear reason="damage">ώ</unclear>
		<lb n="5" type="worddiv"/>σας</w> <w lemma="ἐνθάδε">ἐνθάδε</w>
		<lb n="6"/><w lemma="κατάκειμαι"><orig reg="κατάκειται">κατάκιτε</orig></w>
		</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab>Zoetos, son of Theopemptos, who strove for the blessed life, lies here.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See <xref type="eAla-text" n="IX.43">IX.43</xref> and for this man's brother see <xref type="inscription" n="169" href="130158">13.158</xref> and discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="IX.42">IX.42</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p><rs type="found">Stray find.</rs>.  <rs type="origLocation">Unknown.</rs>. <rs type="lastLocation">Museum.</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

